pageContext.claim: “We beat predictions more than three times the highest estimate that I saw during the campaign. Nobody thought it was even possible to get close to a 7 million number. Two million was maxed out, if you were lucky and if you did a great job.”
pageContext.analysis: The rate of job gains has been largely consistent from the Obama to Trump administrations, belying his claim that few thought it was possible to add more than 6 million jobs by this point.
